	   <tr><td colspan=2>hi there, <br><br>I am a L38 Halfling Druid that needs a little help.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am looking for a decent place to solo for XP and, hopefully, not have to fight off alot of other groups/players for the mob.  I have tried RM doing HGs, but they are way too camped.<br><br>Also, I have never quad kited as I dont have the timing to snare 4 mobs at the same time and get them all close together.  I usually Root/DOT my targets and sit relatively close.  This is another reason that I dont want to have alot of other people in the area.<br><br>I have not solo'd since about L34 when I was doing Mammoths in EF.  I have been running with a guild group (consisting of L50 ranger, L42 ranger, L42 monk, L38 Druid(me), and sometimes the the 42 monk was replaced by a 34 cleric) lately.<br><br>If you could also give me some strategies to get my Veeshan faction up (need to be able to run past woushi to get group GD Port) that would be appreciated too,<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
