	   <tr><td colspan=2>Since you dont want to quad kite I wont be able to tell you where to go, I have quad since 34 constantly.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its the best exp you would get, and timing is a matter of practice, my advice would be to practice it, and at your lvl go to IC to quad kite wolves (cougars shouldnt be good exp anymore)or to Overthere. This last zone can be a good one to root/dot until 40 too.<br><br>What I can tell you is how to raise your Veeshan faction quickly. Have posted about this before in this forum and in factions forum under Veeshans one, you can look there for more details.<br><br>Strategy to raise that faction is simple, go to Great Divide, sow yourself and run around wizzy spires snaring all the frost giants and Drakkel Wolves you see around.  When you run out of mana go to a save place (sitting by or under waterfall that leads to Thurgadin is pretty safe) and just sit to med, dont zone out of GD, stay there in a safe place like the one I mentioned.  You will get all the faction hits when other people kill the giants and wolves you snared before. If there are 2 or 3 groups hunting there (fort, spires and totem for example) you will get TONS of faction hits in almost no time at all.<br><br>Of course, you can try to raise faction killing those wolves and giants yourself, but trust me, you will have to spend at least 50 hours doing so to get your faction with Veeshan to dubious that way.<br><br>Hope this help you.<br><br>Asuran<br>Lvl 55 preserver<br>E´ci<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Jun  7 13:15:35 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
